[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there any chance we can get some variant of <code>{L | R}</code> to work on games?</p>",
        "id": 484779159,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732732793
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the most basic version of this notation would simply be <code>{xl | xr}</code> for <code>mk L R xl xr</code></p>",
        "id": 484779300,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732732841
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But it'd be nice to also support some syntax for <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SetTheory.PGame.ofLists#doc\">docs#SetTheory.PGame.ofLists</a>, perhaps <code>{[a, b, c] | [x, y, z]}</code> for <code>ofLists [a, b, c] [x, y, z]</code>?</p>",
        "id": 484779382,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732732875
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm thinking we could also have something like <code>{i ↦ f i | j ↦ g j}</code> as mechanisms to specify the two functions in the constructor, but I don't know if this is feasible / desirable</p>",
        "id": 484780040,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732733144
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think this would collide with set notation</p>",
        "id": 484780547,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1732733371
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, of course</p>",
        "id": 484780572,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732733385
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there some other unicode bracket we can use?</p>",
        "id": 484780605,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732733396
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>maybe <code>⦃⦄</code>?</p>",
        "id": 484780854,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1732733495
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was thinking about that</p>",
        "id": 484780877,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732733505
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>｛｝</code> would be horrible, and <code>﹛﹜</code> probably isn't good either</p>",
        "id": 484781057,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1732733576
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Although, isn't this used as some sort of variant of <code>{x}</code> for implicit arguments?</p>",
        "id": 484781078,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732733585
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As in <code>∀ ⦃x⦄, _</code></p>",
        "id": 484781118,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732733605
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is, yes, but as they're used in completely different places (in particular, one is a term and the other isn't), I hope collision can be avoided</p>",
        "id": 484781145,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1732733622
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We could also use <code>g{ L | R }</code>, I guess</p>",
        "id": 484781261,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1732733655
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, that might actually be better</p>",
        "id": 484781282,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732733666
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Because it means we can define this notation for different kinds of games with different prefixes</p>",
        "id": 484781305,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1732733677
    }
]